Firestone Tire and Rubber Co saidChairman John Nevin entered into a new employment agreementallowing him to continue as an executive or consultant with thecompany until he becomes 65 years old in February 1992.    Firestone said Nevin has agreed to remain as chiefexecutive officer until its board elects a successor. Thecompany was not immediately available for comment.   In the release, Firestone said while Nevin serves as chiefexecutive, he will be paid his current salary and will continueto be eligible for supplemental compensation.    Firestone said Nevin will serve as a consultant to thecompany after a new chief executive is found and until Nevinbecomes 65. Firestone said it agreed that during this period,Nevin will be paid a fee not less than the pension which hewould have been entitled to if he retired.    It also said Nevin agreed not to engage in a competitivebusiness until he becomes 67.    On February 17, Firestone granted Nevin an option to buy100,000 shares of the company's common at 34.19 dlrs a share. Reuter&#3;